column5: I musta been a good boy this year  Here's what i got  Shimano Compre rod  MH Fast 7' Shimano Curado 300E reel 150 bucks in Sail Gift Cards Gold Bracelet Fliieting gloves Fish Handleing gloves Wincester hunting knife  Heres what i gave her  Diamond earings Timex watch TomTom Gps Warm slippers 100 bucks in  Gift Cards Hot Paws Gloves 2 turtleneck tops  so what did ya get !!!!
Santa got me a Moultrie D55IR Game/Spy camera... so I can show Marty and Brian what really roams around the house!!
Nice !!!!!

Santa had me going for a bit, the usually stocking stuffers, some new clothes. No fishing gear , I took a good look around the tree to make sure I didnt miss anything. And whamoo! A 42 in flat screen TV hiding in the back Thanks Santa
Santa brought me health, happiness, another year with the sexiest actress/model in Toronto.

Joulupukki brought me the necessities of winter living.  Warm socks longjohns warm clothes a toque and gloves ice fishing jigs  More importantly, a family together under one roof, and day 2 of the feast.
ok Ok I ll bite first, we wanna see pictures lol

A brand new grandson, All of the kids (except the one that had the baby) at home with their grandmothers having a wonderful dinner. And the usual gift cards clothes and toys/clothes galore for the 3 little ones. And most of all our health.

well Santa was by and i got a signed copy of Daves book couple of magazines pair of spoons and some ice gloves oh 50.00 at BPS(really good since my Santa knows very little about fishing) along with clothes.

well, this year I gave my wife and her parents a trip to California so my father-in-law could see his father who is getting over a broken leg. So my wife did a hell of a lot of shopping and my daughter got to go to Disneyland which was awesome.  For me I got a Canon 60D and a Sigma 120-400mm lens
I was all excited to pull a Frabill Tru-Trax net out of a big long box shipped from LeBaron...only to find the hoop had been crushed in transit.  At least everyone is healthy!

Well Santa was good to us this year, and along with some lovely jewellery, here are the fishing related items we got.  Paul got me this nifty pair of HEATED boots from Columbia      I got Paul a few musky hats     Some Helly Hansen Under Armour      An Eddie Bauer Folding Shovel and Fog Off sponge      I also got him a few funny posters for his man cave     Love this one!        I haven't drawn in over 25 years, so decided to give it a whirl again and took pencil to paper and drew Paul from a picture with one of his Lakair Musky.     Merry Chritmas All.  May you all have a healthy, happy and prosperous New Year!!!!  Joey

No fishing gear, but frankly, I buy what I want when I want it. And I'd rather pick out my own stuff than pretend to be thrilled with what other people pick out.  On the other hand I was thrilled with the Pro 5 Kitchenaid stand mixer I got. With it were a pasta roller/cutter, a sausage stuffer, a meat grinder and a slicer/dicer attachment all driven off the main unit. Pretty cool. I actually picked it all out thinking I was doing it for a gift for our son who has recently, with his gf/partner, gotten into cooking. They were very pleased with theirs as well.  I also got a beautiful glazed cast iron casserole that I've been wanting for a while. I think it's very nifty to be able to use one pot to sear or precook stuff on the stove top and then just transfer to the oven to finish cooking. Besides, good cast iron is the way to go for cooking many things, and it's great exercise lifting those heavy pots and pans.  The other notable gift is a plastic moose that lifts his tail and poops out brown jelly beans when you press down on his back. For some reason my wife doesn't think it looks nice on the coffee table in a grove of stained glass evergreen trees that our son made years ago with a little guidance from my sister.  JF
Cute eh!!!    Just kidding
i got a new g loomis rainsuit and quantum smoke pt reel. some clothes, couple rapala baits. she got a new laptop.... thats im using... lol
i got a "new to me" 2003 Dodge ram - 2 dr with full cap... certified and safetied.... $2k... and the missus paid for it a few days bfore christmas ....  tranny was going on the van....

We agreed not to spend anything on each other , just stocking fillers. Got another jigging rap thrown in.  AThis year was all about our baby boy (21 months). The wife and I dont exchange this time of year.It,s all about the kiddies.  We got to spend today with grandkids in a bag.LOL     Shes a real ham.   THATS ALL I / WE NEEDED FOR CHRISTMAS.   J,very nice gift to Paul.
Outdoors wise, I got a Daiwa Luna 203 baitasting reel and a Buck Ergo Pro knife.
Santa took mercy on me and my sick addiction to fishing and didn't get me anything outdoor related..

lol!  Too many trolls... You'll have to check out next month's issue of Wed Luxe Magazine.  She will be on the cover  We exchanged gifts with the other side of the family... I got 2 st croix ice fishing rods, some ice tackle and a new ski jacket.  I am pretty much set for all my winter sports!  Ada and I decided to splurge this year and we bought ourselves an HD camcorder.  Fishing videos to come!

Santa was good to me this year   my daughter gave me an Ipod.... my very first     She got me a game for the WII console .... NHL Slapshot which we played into the wee hours of Christmas night   and a new Disturbed album that is going to be awesome for the upcoming fishing videos  Now the IPOD is loaded to the max Leechman

Nothing, Nada, Zip, Bupkiss..................... So I got myself some goodies.  In October I bought a Panasonic P50G20 50" plasma and walnut stand. I added a Panasonic BLU Ray player and have a pair of Pinacle 10" 125 watt powered subs and a Yamaha HTR6295 Networked/3D 7.2 channel surround sound receiver on order. They were sold out of the center channel speaker I was after and the rears will have to wait for the bank account to refill some. The subs were 75% off and the receiver was 50% off.
